## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> ### 1. Person Filmography — Pre-built Index
> Loading [title.principals.tsv](file:///D:/Evolve_Robot_Lab/Project/FilmDB_Demo/kb/IMDb/title.principals.tsv/title.principals.tsv) (98M rows, 4.2 GB) at runtime is not feasible. I propose adding a pre-built `person_index.parquet` during KB mapping. This adds ~3-5 minutes to the pipeline and ~50-100 MB of disk. **Is this acceptable?**

> [!IMPORTANT]
> ### 2. KB-First vs. API-First Routing
> The plan makes **KB tools primary** ([required](file:///D:/Evolve_Robot_Lab/Project/FilmDB_Demo/backend/app/governance.py#64-70)) and **API tools optional** (fallback). This means:
> - Movie lookups hit local parquet first (instant) — API only used if KB has no match
> - Similarity uses tag-based matching from ML data — TMDB API as fallback
> - Reviews come from local RT data — RT API as fallback
>
> **Are you okay with KB-first routing, or do you want both KB and API to always run in parallel?**

> [!IMPORTANT]
> ### 3. Additional Changes Beyond the Update Doc
> Beyond what the architecture doc specifies, I want to update:
> - **Entity Resolver** — attach [imdb_id](file:///D:/Evolve_Robot_Lab/Project/FilmDB_Demo/rag/kb_mapping.py#68-74) in the resolution step so all tools get it for free
> - **Routing Matrix** — update existing intents (ENTITY_LOOKUP, TOP_RATED, RECOMMENDATION, REVIEWS, COMPARISON) to prefer KB tools
> - **Governance** — register all 7 new KB tools
> - **Tool Formatter** — add LLM-friendly summaries for KB tool outputs
>
> Should I proceed with all of these, or keep the scope limited to only the new tools?

> [!WARNING]
> ### 4. COMPARISON Intent — Two-Entity Extraction
> The current [EntityResolver](file:///D:/Evolve_Robot_Lab/Project/FilmDB_Demo/backend/app/entity_resolver.py#117-148) only extracts **one** entity. For `MOVIE_COMPARISON`, we need **two** movie titles. The [IntentAgent](file:///D:/Evolve_Robot_Lab/Project/FilmDB_Demo/backend/app/intent_agent.py#75-155) already extracts multiple entities in its `entities[]` array, but the resolver only uses `entities[0]`. I'll update the comparison flow to extract both entities from the intent. **Any concerns?**

